# Security Policy

Per `docs/10-knowledge-management-and-security-policy.md`:

- Secrets load from `.env` or environment injection — never commit or log them
- Authorization checked at application-service boundary before data access
- Retrieval queries MUST include ownership, visibility, and sensitivity filters
- External LLM calls require policy decision (source, sensitivity, purpose)
- Logs contain identifiers and diagnostics — not full documents, credentials, or unrestricted prompts
- Restricted content stays local unless explicitly authorized

## Data classification

Every source and derived object has owner, visibility, and sensitivity (public, internal, confidential, restricted).

## Prohibited in committed code

- API keys, tokens, passwords
- Real `.env` values (use `.env.example` with placeholders)
- Hardcoded session secrets
